<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Wrestling President Dies in Car Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Ivan Iaryguine, president of the
Russian wrestling federation, was killed in a car crash, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Iaryguine, who was 49, died following the crash in the Russian
Caucasus on Saturday night close to the town of Neftekoumsk in the
Stavropol region, the report said.
</P>
<P>
He was on his way from Makhachkala in Dagestan, where he was
guest of honnour at a wrestling competition, to his home in
Kislovodsk.
</P>
<P>
Iaryguine was the world freestyle wrestling champion in 1973
and twice Olympic champion, in 1972 and 1976. He was also the
chief coach of the former Soviet Union freestyle wrestling teams
in the 1980s.  
</P>
</TEXT>
