<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Coach Sacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia coach Eduardo
Vingada was sacked on Sunday after the narrow 1-0 victory over
Qatar in a World Cup qualifier.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese will be replaced by German Otto Pfeister for the
remainder of the qualifying competition, a report reaching said.
</P>
<P>
The Saudis currently lies second in Asian Zone Group B, level
on seven points with China after four games. Iran leads the table
with eight points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
