<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Hospitals to Get Extra Funding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- British hospitals will receive
an emergency cash injection of around 250 million pounds (402
million US dollars) to tackle the problem of growing patient
queues this winter.
</P>
<P>
The government is expected to announce the decision this week,
local press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The number of patients on the waiting lists has risen by 10
percent to a record 1.15 million in England in the past year and
some of emergency treatment and other operations are facing
cancellation because of cash shortages.
</P>
<P>
Most of the support funds is expected to be found from cuts
in the defense and trade and industry budgets, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The medical society sees the money as welcome relief, though it
claims that more than 500 million pounds (805 million US dollars)
is needed to deal with the difficult situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
