<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Prime Minister Returns Home from London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Crown Prince and
Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Sabah returned home
today after a seven-month health recovering in London.
</P>
<P>
He was welcomed at the airport by Kuwaiti Emir Sheikh Jaber
Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah and high ranking officials in a grand ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti prime minister suffered a bleeding in the colon and
undertook an operation in March at home. Later he was flown to
London where he underwent further surgeries and has since been
recuperating there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
