<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK PM to Visit Northern Ireland Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Northern Ireland
Office confirmed today that Prime Minister Tony Blair will visit
the province Monday.
</P>
<P>
Blair is expected to meet representatives of all sides involved
in the Northern Ireland peace talks, including Gerry Adams, leader
of Sinn Fein, the political wing of the Irish Republican Army
(IRA).
</P>
<P>
On his second visit to Northern Ireland since he became Prime
Minister in May, Blair +will be visiting various parts of the
province, and will be meeting a fairly wide range of people+, said
a government source.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that attention will focus on any encounter
between Blair and Gerry Adams as such a meeting would be the first
between a British Prime Minister and the Sinn Fein leader since
the current wave of unrest started 28 years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
