<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Police Seize Two Suspected Bandits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Two suspected bandits
were shot wounded by police in Zanzibar on Saturday evening when
they were attempting to escape arrest.
</P>
<P>
The police are holding the suspects, along with their three
accomplices.
</P>
<P>
Detectives said they were tailing the suspects who had arrived
on the Indian isles by a boat from the Tanzanian capital of Dar
es Salaam last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar Urban West Regional Police Commander Mussa Msheba
declined to give details, saying the matter has "not yet been
taken to court."
</P>
<P>
The suspects, whose legs were wounded, are said to have come
from Arusha in northern Tanzania acting on a mission.
</P>
<P>
Detectives later searched a house in which the suspects had
stayed but found nothing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
