<HEADLINE> Israel Erects Checkpoints Again At Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Israeli forces erected
checkpoints again early this morning at the entrances of West Bank
city of Hebron and reinforced checking of identity documents and
vehicles, the Palestinian News Agency WAFA said.
</P>
<P>
Local residents have to show their identity documents to the
Israeli forces before entering into or coming out from the city
and the vehicles were searched thoroughly, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli forces treated people in a barbaric way, it quoted
local residents as saying.
</P>
<P>
Hebron is about 50 kilometers south of Jerusalem. Israel
tightened security measures after it arrested outside Jerusalem
shortly after midnight Thursday two Palestinians from Hebron who
were found to have some 50 kilograms of explosives in their car.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli police said that they have not ruled out
nationalist motives, but they believe the suspects intended to
sell the explosives to the Jewish contractors, from whom they had
been stolen.
</P>
<P>
Based on the confessions of the suspects, Israeli police and
defense forces raided a building near Hebron Friday afternoon,
where they found 30 kilograms of explosives.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security experts have confirmed the explosives were not
the type used in the suicide bomb attacks in Jerusalem on July 30
and September 4, which killed 26 people and wounded hundreds
others.
</P>
<P>
An explosion in the vegetable market close to a Jewish quarter
in Hebron created panic on Saturday. The Israeli police said that
the explosion may have been caused by a stun grenade thrown by an
Israeli soldier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
