<HEADLINE> Siemens Marks 150th Birthday with Record Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest electronics and
engineering group Siemens AG marked its 150 anniversary of
founding today with record business performance.
</P>
<P>
Its sales over the past fiscal year have topped 100 billion
German marks (57 billion U.S. dollars), the first time in history.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Siemens chief executive Heinrich von
Pierer at a company ceremony in Berlin today.
</P>
<P>
