that the company would continue to concentrate on its traditional
and most profitable business of electronics and electrical
engineering, while avoiding any expansions prone to losses.
</P>
<P>
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl, who was also present, praised
Siemens for its consistent courage for innovations and said the
company was an example showing how German firms could gain a
foothold in future markets. 
