<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-12 20:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Policemen Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Two policemen were killed when
a group of gunmen opened fire on a police vehicle in southeastern
Turkey last night, the Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place at 23:00, local time, in Lice,
Diyarbarkir Province while the vehicle drove the police home.
</P>
<P>
Two other policemen were wounded and rushed to a nearby hospital
for emergency treatment.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsible for the incident so far, but
police suspected the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) of
this attack.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Saturday, the PKK rebels reportedly attacked a
military post in northern Black Sea town of Giresun, killing
nine soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Eight rebels were killed in the cross-fire with the government
troops.
</P>
<P>
The PKK rebels, which has been fighting a 13-year-old war
against the Turkish government in southeastern Turkey, are trying
to build new bases in the Black Sea region, local reports
said earlier.
</P>
<P>
At present, around 15,000 Turkish troops are fighting the PKK
militants in a cross-border operation in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
A total of 797 PKK rebels have been killed since Turkish
troops, backed by jet bombers and artillery fire, entered northern
Iraq late last month to wipe out the newly built PKK camps
there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
