<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Early Negotiations Across Taiwan Straits Urged (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This has fully demonstrated the determination of the CPC and
the Chinese government, which have been working for many years to
make cross-Straits negotiations possible and to promote peaceful
reunification of the motherland with a practical attitude, sincere
manner, and flexible methods.
</P>
<P>
If cross-Straits relations are to be improved, the two sides
should exchange views on major problems affecting the development
of relations and find ways to solve the differences by following
the One China principle.
</P>
<P>
A non-governmental organization, the Association for Relations
Across the Taiwan-Straits, was approved for discussing routine
matters with Taiwan's Foundation for Exchanges Across Taiwan
Straits and these discussions have played an important role in
promoting the development of cross-Straits relations and
safeguarding the rights and interests of compatriots on both sides.
</P>
<P>
However, the Taiwan side has repeatedly raised political issues
like "Judicial Jurisdiction" to hinder the progress of the talks.
</P>
<P>
The major problems faced by the two bodies are political
issues, and if political differences are not exposed and ways to
solve them are not found, even discussions of routine matters will
produce no satisfactory results.
</P>
<P>
There can be favorable conditions for realizing the peaceful
reunification of the two sides, and the stability and development
of cross-Straits relations can be achieved by holding
cross-Straits negotiations as soon as possible under the One China
principle.
</P>
</TEXT>
