<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Able to Maintain Stability, Prosperity: Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa today told
participants of the East Asia Economic Summit that Hong Kong
people have full confidence in maintaining stability and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a keynote speech at the opening dinner of the Summit
organized by the World Economic Forum, Tung said that it has been
more than three months since Hong Kong became an SAR of China on
July 1, and things have been going quite well, with people's
confidence in the future rising to a historical high.
</P>
<P>
"We in Hong Kong are moving forward with pride and confidence.
Pride in that we are reunited with China and become masters of our
own destiny; confidence in that we can and we will make our city
an even better place going forward," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the economy continues to grow, the financial
foundation remains solid, the society remains pluralistic, the
politicians continue to debate openly on all the topical subjects,
and the many interest groups continue to express their opinions
through many demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
He said that maintaining financial stability is very
challenging, but it can be done. Hong Kong's financial policies
and institutions must operate in a prudent manner to maintain
public confidence. The banking and financial systems must be sound
and healthy to withstand external shocks or policy adjustments.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that Hong Kong will remain secure from the financial
turmoil that some East Asian countries have recently experienced.
</P>
<P>
"For us here in Hong Kong we will continue to pursue sound and
sustainable macro economic policies, which support the stability
of the financial system. This means continued pursuit of the
fiscal discipline which has been a hallmark of Hong Kong in the
past. We shall remain our guideline that government expenditure
over time will grow at a rate no faster than the economy," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that fiscal prudence is a necessary precondition for
exchange rate stability and it shall remain a key of Hong Kong's
economic policy to maintain the link between the Hong Kong dollar
and the US dollar. This gives the confidence in the currency to
the people of Hong Kong and those who do business and invest in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Despite one or two short-lived speculative attacks during the
recent currency upheavals, the Hong Kong dollar has remained rock
solid. We aim to keep it that way," he said, adding that the large
stock of foreign exchange reserves of 82 billion U.S. dollars and
good economic fundamentals of Hong Kong provide the means to do
so, and Hong Kong can also rely on the unwavering support of the
motherland in this objective.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong will continue its policy of law and
predictable tax structure, continue to adhere to the present legal
system and the rule of law to reassure that Hong Kong continues to
provide an even-handed, corruption-free and secure business
environment.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the solid promises of the Basic Law is
fundamental for Hong Kong people's confidence.
</P>
<P>
Tung also explained to participants the electoral affairs of
Hong Kong SAR in the coming few years.
</P>
<P>
The Summit was opened today through Wednesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
