<HEADLINE> Nepal's Cabinet Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister Surya
Bahadur Thapa expanded his cabinet today, one week after he took
office as head of the country's new coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Thapa inducted 13 new ministers and five ministers of state to
his cabinet, bringing to 24 the cabinet members from six, said a
communique issued by King Birendra's Principal Press Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Most of the new faces come from Thapa's own National Democratic
Party (RPP) including Home Minister Buddhi Man Tamang and Minister
for Information and Communications Sarbendra Nath Shukla.
</P>
<P>
Sharat Singh Bhandari, an independent, was allocated the
portfolio of minister for youth, sports and culture.
</P>
<P>
The portfolios of foreign minister and finance minister remain
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali Congress (NC), which toppled Chand-led coalition
government on October 4 with a no-confidence motion, will later
join the present coalition of the RPP and the Nepal Sadbhavana
Party.  
</P>
</TEXT>
