<HEADLINE> Pak Reiterates Priority of Good Ties with Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister
Gohar Ayub Khan reiterated toady that the corner stone of
Pakistan's foreign policy is establishing friendly relations with
neighboring countries and promoting global peace and security.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister made the remarks during a meeting with a
group of 20 officers from various countries attending the Staff
Course at the Command and Staff College in Quetta, provincial
capital of Baluchistan.
</P>
<P>
While briefing them on the parameters and objectives of
Pakistan's foreign policy, Ayub Khan said that Pakistan's
friendship with China has been tested in times of needs and
crises.
</P>
<P>
He also highlighted Pakistan's role at the international fora
like the United Nations and the Organization of Islamic Conference
(OIC).
</P>
<P>
Pakistan attaches great importance to OIC countries, he said,
adding that OIC countries must develop their economic relations.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the visiting officers on Pakistan's efforts to
bring about peace in Afghanistan and hold intra-Afghan dialogue
under the auspices of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Pakistan supports a broad-based government in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
On Pakistan's relations with India, he said that Pakistan is
willing to settle all outstanding issues including the core issue
of Jammu and Kashmir with India.  
</P>
</TEXT>
