<HEADLINE> British Queen Meets Indian Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Visiting British Queen
Elizabeth II today met separately with Indian President Kocheril
Raman Narayanan and Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral with both
sides pledging to impart fresh impetus to bilateral ties, the
Press Trust of India (PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
During her half-hour meeting with Narayanan, the queen referred
to the strong presence of the people of Indian origin in the
United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Narayanan said that the Indian-British relations "are today
much stronger than in the past."
</P>
<P>
The queen, who arrived here Sunday night on a week-long state
visit with her husband Prince Phillip, was accorded a ceremonial
welcome here early today.
</P>
<P>
During the 30-minute meeting between the queen and Gujral, it
was stressed that India and the U.K. must accord special attention
to bolster economic ties, the PTI said.
</P>
<P>
Gujral briefed the queen on the thrust being given to economic
reforms and the great potential for expanding trade relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that the visit of the queen was
considered very special here.
</P>
<P>
The queen, who is on her third visit to India, will visit
Armritsar of Punjab state Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
