<HEADLINE> Eritrea Spends US$210 Million in Energy Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Eritrea has so far
invested more than 210 million US dollars in developing energy,
Eritrean Minister of Energy and Mines Tesfai Gebreselassie said.
</P>
<P>
The latest weekly issue of Eritrea Profile quoted
Gebreselassie as saying in Asmara, capital of Eritrea, that there
is growing demand for energy in the country which calls for
increased state expenditure.
</P>
<P>
Over 28 million US dollars has been spent in developing
sources of electricity supply nationwide, research on energy and
exploration of mining and related activities.
</P>
<P>
The minister disclosed that more energy development projects
will get under way in the future.
</P>
<P>
According to Gebreselassie, an average electric consumption in
the country is 45 kw/hr per person per year. Studies show that
this rate, compared with that of other countries, puts Eritrea in
line with the most backward countries. The energy consumption has
risen by 10 percent annually since 1993. 
</P>
