<HEADLINE> Eight Nepalese Drowned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Eight people in Banke
district of mid-western Nepal drowned Sunday afternoon when trying
to release into river the image of Goddess Durga Bhavani, the
symbol of supreme power in Hinduism, the official RSS news agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
One body was found later in the downstream of the river, but
the rest were not found yet, the RSS said.
</P>
