<HEADLINE> Fighting Intensifies in Northern Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Fighting between the Taliban
militia and the anti-Taliban alliance in northern Afghanistan,
particularly in the Kunduz region, has intensified, a report
reaching here tonight from Kabul said.
</P>
<P>
A fierce battle has been going on in the vicinity of Kunduz
airport which is located in a mountainous region, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The anti-Taliban forces are now stationed at the heights
overlooking the Kunduz airport and no flights are possible out of
the airport as it is under siege, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Taliban conceded loss of Tashkargan, a strategic
town about 220 kilometers northwest of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
Tashkargan is on a strategic road leading to the major northern
city of Mazar-e-Sharif, the stronghold of the anti-Taliban forces.
</P>
<P>
The withdrawal from Tashkargan by the Taliban has opened the
road to Mazar-e-Sharif, making it easier for the anti-Taliban
forces to transport its troops as well as weapons across the
north.  
</P>
</TEXT>
