<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 14:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns USS Nimitz's Arrival in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Iran today condemned the
arrival of the nuclear-powered U.S. aircraft carrier Nimitz in
the Persian Gulf, calling it a "major source of tension" in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The USS Nimitz geared up into the Gulf Sunday night with its
battle group of six warships, as Iran was halfway in its naval
exercises code-named "Piroozi (Victory) 8" in the waters further
north.
</P>
<P>
"The American warships are the sole source of threats in the
region," Iran's Defense Minister Ali Shamkhani said aboard his
command ship "Tunb" off Iran's southern port city of Bushehr,
according to the official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
"Termination of tensions in the Persian Gulf is possible only
through the departure of the U.S. and other foreign warships from
the region," he said, urging the regional countries to cooperate
toward a new security arrangement in the strategic area.
</P>
<P>
The Nimitz and its battle group reinforced eight destroyers,
frigates and other U.S. warships already in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Iran's war games headquarters said the army and the Islamic
Revolution Guards Corps today staged a marine parade of 120
warships, cruisers, destroyers, torpedo boats, speed boats,
logistic warships as well as two Russian-made submarines, and some
40 fighter-bombers and helicopters demonstrated their combat power.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister and a number of senior military
commanders inspected the parade. IRNA said Victory 8 maneuvers
will enter into the fourth stage (tactical stage) from tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Shamkhani as dismissing the U.S. concern over Iran's
maneuvers as part of its propaganda campaign aimed to justify its
illegitimate presence in the region.
</P>
<P>
"Iran's defense doctrine is geared toward elimination of the
sources of tension external to the region. We never consider our
Muslim brothers in the Arab states as a threat to the Islamic
Iran," Shamkhani said.
</P>
<P>
He added "The Victory 8 joint naval maneuvers are within the
scope of the previously announced annual exercises by Iran's armed
forces."
</P>
<P>
He also predicted that "beyond any doubts, the protest by the
Muslim nations of the region against the U.S. warships' polluting
presence would take new dimensions in the future."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the environmental group Green Front of Iran (Green
Peace) today condemned the Nimitz's presence in the Gulf. saying
it contributes to increasing pollution in the Gulf through various
thermal, sound and nuclear pollutants.
</P>
<P>
It urged environmental activists to call on all international
organizations and bodies to declare the Gulf as an area free of
nuclear weapons and confrontation and demand an end to U.S. naval
operations in the region.
</P>
<P>
According to IRNA, Iranian fishermen in the southern provinces
of Khuzestan, Bushehr, Hormuzgan and Sistan and Baluchistan have
strongly protested against the presence of the Nimitz and its
creation of pollution to the water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
