<HEADLINE> EU Official Calls for Dynamism, Innovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) is
calling for dynamic, innovative and stable European enterprises
with international outlooks.
</P>
<P>
Christos Papoutsis, EU commissioner responsible for small and
medium-sized enterprises (SME), made the call today at the fifth
annual SME conference of the Union of Industrial and Employers'
Confederations of Europe (UNICE).
</P>
<P>
"We should more actively encourage an enterprise culture," the
commissioner said, adding that this great potential in particular
sectors like the social economy needed to be unlocked.
</P>
<P>
Papoutsis said Europe should specify those sectors where SME
could play a significant role and should "pay particular
attention" to the structurally changing sectors. He set a new
agenda at the conference for improving and simplifying the EU
business environment.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises and the social partners should join in their
efforts to make enterprises productive and competitive, and to
achieve the required balance between flexibility and security in
labor market, Papoutsis emphasized.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner also announced the state of development,
achieved by the EU's executive body, the European Commission, of a
new financial system to provide support for the creation of
cross-border joint ventures by SMEs within the EU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
