<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets With Antigua and Barbuda Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng held
talks with visiting Prime Minister Lester Bird of Antigua and
Barbuda here today.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcomed to Bird, Li said that the two countries
have conducted fruitful cooperation in all fields since they set
up diplomatic relations in 1983.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the current visit by Prime
Minister Bird will deepen mutual understanding and push forward
friendly cooperative relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li appreciated Antigua and Barbuda for its taking the lead to
adopt and sticking to the position of "one China" in the eastern
Caribbean region.
</P>
<P>
Bird said that during his first visit to China 12 years ago, he
was impressed by the respect that China shows to a small country
at the other side of the globe.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country always holds that the Government of
the People's Republic of China is the sole legitimate government
that represents China. He said that his country was the first
among eastern Caribbean countries to recognize that there is only
one China in the world. It will stick to this position in the
future.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the government of his country will
unswervingly push forward the deepening of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that China is a developing country that
cherishes friendly feelings toward the peoples of other developing
countries. China has always lent sympathy and support to them for
their efforts to build their own countries and provided them with
assistance within its capacity.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both China and Antiqua and Barbuda are faced with
common task of developing their own economies. Both countries are
trying to explore the new ways and fields for their cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Bird thanked the Chinese Government and people for providing
assistance to his country in the fields of agriculture, culture
and urban development. He noted that economic and trade
cooperation between the two countries has a bright future. He
welcomes Chinese entrepreneurs to go to his country for
cooperation. He also hopes that the two peoples will strengthen
exchanges and deepen mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
Later, Li and Bird signed an agreement on economic and
technology cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Li Peng presided over a welcoming ceremony
for Bird, who are here for an official visit to China. This
evening, Li hosted a dinner for him and his party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
