<HEADLINE> Israel Releases 9 Jordanian Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Israel released today
another nine Jordanian prisoners in a bid to show the gesture
of goodwill to Jordan.
</P>
<P>
All the nine Jordanians were being transported to Jordan
today by the Israeli military helicopter, an Israeli army
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
It said that these Jordanians were not related to the
activities of the Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) and they
will continue their prison services in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli-Jordanian relationship has been damaged by
Israeli intelligence agents' failed assassination of Hamas
leader Khaled Mashaal last month in Amman.
</P>
<P>
Some media reports said that Jordan has suspended its security
cooperation with Israel, but the Israeli side has denied that.
</P>
<P>
the Israeli army announcement quoted Defense Minister Yitzhak
Mordechai as saying today that the Israeli army will do its best
to improve Israel's relations with Jordan.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister is going to Jordan again in the near
future for such a purpose, it said.
</P>
<P>
Israel released early this month nine Jordanian prisoners and
sent them back to Jordan under the agreement reached by the two
sides in exchange for the release of the two Israeli agents who
attacked Mashaal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
