<HEADLINE> Nordic Banks Merge Into Largest Regional Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's third largest bank,
Nordbanken, and Finland's main bank, Merita Bank, announced their
merger today.
</P>
<P>
The merger creates the Nordic region's largest banking group,
which is worth more than 10 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish part owns 60 percent of stocks of the newly created
Meritanorbanken and the Finnish part 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Merita bank was formed in June 1995 from the merger of
several large commercial banks in Finland. The Nordbanken was
Sweden's most profitable bank last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
