<HEADLINE> Teenager Claims Weightlifting Title in World Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Teenager Li Zhuo claimed the
women's 50-kg weightlifting title with world records at the Eighth
National Games here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old strongwoman of Liaoning province, snatched 95
kgs and jerked up 122.5 kgs for a total of 217.5 kgs, all beating
the listed world records.
</P>
<P>
The previous snatch mark of 88 kgs was set by Jiang Baoyu in
the Asian Weightlifting Championships in 1995 in Pusan, while the
jerk record of 110.5 kgs was set by Liu Xiuhua in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Five other women lifters also bettered the snatch record, while
both Li Yuanli and Liu Xiuhua also surpassed the three marks.
</P>
