<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets With S. Arabian Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- China and Saudi Arabia enjoy
enormous potential for cooperation in the petrochemical sector,
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo said today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Saudi Arabian Minister of Petroleum and
Mineral Resources Ali Bin Ibrahim Al-N'aimi, Wu said that the two
countries have had good relations, which will promote the
development of bilateral economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government appreciates various forms
of cooperation between the China Petrochemical Corporation and the
Saudi Arabia National Oil Company, and backs the two companies in
establishing a direct, long-term and stable cooperative
relationship in oil resources. He invited Saudi Arabia to invest
in upgrading Chinese oil refineries.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted that with the expansion of the Chinese economy,
China's demand for petrochemical products will increase steadily,
and that the import of crude oil from different countries and
channels has become an important component of China's strategy on
resources.
</P>
<P>
Al-N'aimi said that the Saudi Arabian government pays close
attention to increasing economic and trade cooperation with China,
especially in the petrochemical sector.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the two countries will tap new channels
of cooperation. 
</P>
