<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Vice-President of European Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji
today voiced his appreciations and thanks to the Commission of the
European Union (EU) and its vice-president Leon Brittan for the
efforts they have made in supporting China's entry into the World
Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Brittan and his party here this afternoon,
Zhu cited the EU as China's important economic partner and said
his country hopes that bilateral cooperation in every field,
especially in economy and trade sector, will expand continuously.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Zhu also briefed the EU visitors on China's
economic situation and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Brittan expressed his admirations to China's fast economic
growth with a low inflation rate. Moreover, he expressed the hope
of the EU to make joint efforts with China to bring bilateral
cooperation in various areas to a new stage.
</P>
<P>
The EU vice-president reaffirmed that the EU supports China's
access to the WTO at an early date.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also exchanged views on other issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi, Chinese minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, was present at the meeting.  
</P>
