<HEADLINE> Beijing Culture Week Features Arab Culture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A five-day culture week
featuring cultures of six Gulf nations opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The culture week is jointly sponsored by the Chinese Ministry
of Culture and the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC), which is
composed of Oman, the United Arab Emirates, Kuwait, Bahrain, Saudi
Arabia and Qatar.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time the GCC holds such a cultural event in
China.
</P>
<P>
The culture week includes exhibitions of handicrafts, song and
dance shows, seminars, and TV programs from the six nations.
</P>
<P>
He Luli, vice-chairwoman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference National Committee, and Abdulaziz
Al-Jallal, representative of the GCC, were present at today's
opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony, Chinese Vice-Minister of Culture Meng
Xiaosi and Al-Jallal hailed the development of friendly relations
between China and the GCC in culture and other areas.
</P>
<P>
They expressed the belief that the culture week will help
increase the mutual understanding and friendship between the
peoples of China and the six countries.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic envoys of the six GCC nations attended the opening
ceremony together with several hundred people from all walks of
life in Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
