<HEADLINE> Sasakawa Japan-China Friendship Fund Holds Meeting in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Sasakawa Japan-China
Friendship Fund held the 22nd meeting of its executive committee
here today.
</P>
<P>
Members attending the committee shared their view that the
Sasakawa Japan-China Friendship Fund should further increase the
contacts and communications between the teenagers of both
countries, thus playing a bigger role in training and upbringing
successors for Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
The Sasakawa Japan-China Friendship Fund, founded jointly in
1989 by the Japan Sasakawa Peace Foundation (SPF) and the China
Association for International Friendly Contact (CAIFC), is the
largest special fund involving in non-governmental exchanges
between China and Japan. Its total amount stands at 10 billion yen.
</P>
