<HEADLINE> China Will Continue to Work for Middle East Peace: CPC Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- An official of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) said here today that China will continue to
work for the peaceful settlement of the Middle East issue.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, told a delegation of the National Democratic Party of
Egypt that China hopes to see early settlement of the Middle East
issue on the basis of relevant resolutions of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
China has "always supported the just struggle of the
Palestinian people," he added.
</P>
<P>
Wen, also member of the secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, expressed admiration to Egypt's "positive role" in
enhancing unity among Arab and African nations and in helping
resolve the Middle East issue.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes China and Egypt would strengthen cooperation
in maintaining world peace and striving for the establishment of a
new international political and economic order.
</P>
<P>
The CPC official noted that China and Egypt, the CPC and the
National Democratic Party, have maintained friendly relations
since the two countries set up diplomatic ties 41 years ago.
</P>
<P>
He said the current trip of the National Democratic Party
delegation will help promote the development of the friendly ties
between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Kamal El-Shazli, deputy secretary-general of the National
Democratic Party and head of the delegation, extended
congratulations over the success of the 15th CPC National Congress
and said he hopes the friendly relations between the National
Democratic Party and the CPC would continue to develop.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed appreciation of China's stand in supporting
the just cause of the Palestinians and the Arab people.
</P>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, held talks with El-Shazli and his delegation
earlier today.  
</P>
