<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
stronger today, enjoying the benefit of U.S. investor interest and
buying related to the purchase of the Victorian government's
Power-Net electricity transmission network by U.S. energy company
GPU Inc.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 73.82 U.S. cents, up from 73.63
last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Traders noted buying of Australian dollars today by major
institutions involved in the Power-Net transaction.
</P>
<P>
The network is being purchased by GPU for 1.87 billion U.S.
dollars, in addition to license fees with a present value of 118.3
million U.S. dollars payable to the government over the period of
December 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
However, traders said that the currency looked a little
vulnerable after failing to move through the psychologically
important 74 U.S. cents level during the day.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar ended at 89.17 from
88.72 against the Japanese yen and at 1.2962 from 1.2841 against
the German mark.  
</P>
