<HEADLINE> Ramos Leaves for Hong Kong, Myanmar, Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
left here today for a five-day visit to Hong Kong, Myanmar and
Laos for closer trade and economic relations with the neighbors.
</P>
<P>
During his first stop in Hong Kong, Ramos will address the
Sixth East Asian Summit of the World Economic Forum on the current
economic situation in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Ramos, who is accompanied by some members of the Cabinet and
Congress and a delegation of businessmen, will also meet with Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
and some business groups.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said in a statement before departure that his state visit
to Myanmar and Laos, the newest members of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), are in fulfillment of the
Philippines' regional responsibilities as the chair of the ASEAN
Standing Committee. 
