<HEADLINE> Cholera Hits Kenya's Third-Largest City, Killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The cholera epidemic has hit
Kenya's third-largest city of Kisumu bordering on Lake Victoria,
killing eight people during the past two days and leaving more
than 30 hospitalized, the Daily Nation reported today.
</P>
<P>
The disease, which has ravaged south-eastern Nyanza Province
and killed more than 200 people within two months, is currently
spreading fast in residential estates and Kisumu's suburbs, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
Local public health officials said persistent lack of clean
drinking water could hasten the spread of the disease, which
kills within hours of attack.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims came from the Kibos, Nyamasaria, Manyatta,
Nyalenda, Obunga and Nyawita areas of the town.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health and Kisumu municipal authorities had
closed down all food stands in the town to prevent the disease
from reaching the area, but all of them have since been
re-opened.
</P>
<P>
Reports said intravenous fluids and necessary drugs are likely
to run out owing to the mounting number of patients. 
</P>
</TEXT>
