<HEADLINE> BA to Start Direct Flights to London from Entebbe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- British Airways (BA) is to
start direct flights from Entebbe near Kampala to London on
October 29 this year, local daily The Monitor reported today.
</P>
<P>
BA Sales Executive Rosette Rugamba was quoted as saying that
"We have normally been going through Nairobi, Kenya to pick more
passengers and cargo but most clients complained and we had to
find a solution."
</P>
<P>
She said BA will start with two flights departing from
Entebbe, Uganda's sole international airport, on Wednesdays and
Sundays.
</P>
<P>
However, she added, the route will include travelling from
Entebbe via Dar es Salaam to London.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to increase to three national flights in February
1998," she said, adding "We are confident that the number of
clients will increase." 
</P>
