<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Leader of European Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met here today with Leon Brittan,
vice-president of the Commission of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views on such issues as Sino-European relations
and China's entry into the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
China has always emphasized its relationship with the European
Union, and is willing to expand its bilateral and multilateral
cooperation with the EU, Qian said.
</P>
