EU would continue its efforts to accelerate the process. Qian also
said he hoped that Brittan's visit would help improve
Sino-European relations.
</P>
<P>
Brittan expressed his pleasure with China's achievements and
the future goals defined by the 15th National Congress of the
Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
EU and China have made great progress in regarding China's
entry into the WTO, he said, and the EU expects an early
resolution of the issues related to the entry. 
