<HEADLINE> Beijing Records Growing Trade with Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese capital city of Beijing
reported an increase of 94.2 percent in bilateral trade with
Singapore during the first eight months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Local trade officials said that the city's trade volume with
Singapore reached 190 million US dollars during the January-August
period, of which 85.34 million dollars were from export, up 110
percent as against the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The bulk of exports were half-finished goods from Singapore
processed in Beijing, like single circuit chips, and telephones
including wireless ones, pagers and CD drivers. And Main import
items from Singapore include kerosene, integrated circuits,
microelectronics, and aircraft or helicopter parts. 
</P>
