<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Commercialise National Railways by </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe government will
commercialise the National Railways by December, Deputy Minister
of Transport and Energy Zenzo Nsimbi said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of the National Railways of Zimbabwe
(NRZ) Sitting Tenants' Association in Bulawayo, the country's
second largest city, Nsimbi said he will push for the
commercialisation of the parastatal in parliament next week.
</P>
<P>
The commercialisation was expected on turning the NRZ into a
profitable organisation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Under the exercise, the parastatal would shed off non-core
businesses like the provision of houses for employees and its
workshops to concentrate on transporting goods and passengers.
</P>
<P>
"In commercialisation, the government will be the sole
shareholder and companies are encouraged to zero in on core
business," Nsimbi noted.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was called to discuss progress made on
negotiations to sell NRZ houses to sitting tenants.
</P>
<P>
NRZ was not opposed to selling the houses to sitting tenants,
he said, adding that the commercialisation might be the opportune
time to dispose of the houses as provision of accommodation was
not NRZ's core business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
