<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Strongwoman Betters World Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongwoman Xing Fen
bettered the world records en route to win the women's 46-kg
category weightlifting title at the Eighth National Games here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese woman of Guangdong province, snatched 85 kgs and
jerked up 117.5 kgs for a total of 202.5 kgs, all surpassing the
listed world marks in the event.
</P>
<P>
The original world mark of 81.5 kgs in snatch was set by her
compatriot Jiang Yinsu in the second East Asian Games in Pusan
early this year, the world record of 105.5 kgs in jerk was created
by Xing Fen herself at the Asian Weightlifting Championships in
July 1997, while the two-lift combined world record of 185 kgs was
set by another Chinese Guang Hong in April, 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
