<HEADLINE> More Foreign-Funded Projects Built in Eastern Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A number of large-scale
foreign-funded enterprises have started construction or become
operational recently in the port city of Ningbo, in east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Those major projects that were built recently included a
petro-chemical firm funded by Esso Co. of the United States at a
cost of 29 million US dollars. It has an annual processing
capacity of 35,000 tons of lubricants, 100,000 tons of oil
products for special use and 12,000 tons of petrochemical products.
</P>
<P>
Another project is a joint furniture manufacturing venture
between Beijing-based Dine Scientific and Technological
Development Company and the Nicos Engineering Company of Italy. It
involves a joint investment of 20 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Thailand-funded Chaitai Cereals and Oil Co. has
formerly gone into operation with an annual processing capacity of
180,000 tons, which involves a total investment of 80 million US
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
