<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Queen Elizabeth Visits India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Queen Elizabeth II of Britain
was today accorded a ceremonial welcome on the fore court of
Rashtrapati Bhavan (the presidential palace of India) here marking
the beginning of her week-long state visit to India, Press Trust
of India (PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
The British monarch, who is on her third visit to this country
together with her husband Prince Phillip, was received by Indian
President Kocheril Raman Narayanan, Prime Minister Inder Kumar
Gujral and his cabinet colleagues.
</P>
<P>
Wearing a deep pink floral silk dress with a matching silk hat,
she inspected a guard of honor by the three services after the
national anthems of the two nations were played by an
inter-services band, PTI said.
</P>
<P>
The queen, who arrived here from Pakistan on Sunday night, was
given a 21-gun salute after she was introduced by President
Narayanan to the ministers and diplomats present on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
Later, she will be going to Raj Ghat (the tomb of Mahatma
Gandhi). Then she will call on the Indian president and also meet
the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The queen will be visiting the city of Amritsar, Punjab,
tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
