<HEADLINE> Nepal's Finance Minister Satisfied With Tibetan Investment Climate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's Minister of Finance
Shukla has shown satisfaction with the Tibetan investment
environment.
</P>
<P>
He was in Tibet recently for the Tibet-Nepal Economic and Trade
Talks '97, where he said that he is familiar with Tibet's
preferential investment policies and that Tibet and Nepal have
similar geographical and economic conditions, and economic and
trade co-operation among them is increasing and that they want it
to grow quicker.
</P>
<P>
The talks shifted the co-operation focus from exchanges of
goods to project co-operation, and the minister said that there
have been problems with project co-operation, but that they have
eventually been solved with the help of the Tibetan regional
government. Recently, Nepal set up 28 joint projects in Tibet and
they are doing well.
</P>
<P>
The minister said he hopes Tibetan enterprises can invest in
Nepal, and that it would be a good opportunity for them to use
Nepal as a transfer point on the way to South Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
He also showed admiration of the economic progress in Tibet.
</P>
</TEXT>
