<HEADLINE> Prime Minister of Antigua and Barbuda Arrives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Lester Bird of
Antigua and Barbuda arrived here this afternoon on an official
visit to China.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister of the Caribbean island nation is here as
guest of Chinese Premier Li Peng. This is his first trip to China
since he took office in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Bird's entourage includes Henderson Simon,
minister of state in the prime minister's office.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Xizheng, vice-minister of power industry and chairman of
the Chinese Government Reception Committee, was among those who
greeted the guests at the airport.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that Premier Li Peng will preside over a welcome
ceremony in honor of Bird and hold talks with him later today.
</P>
