<HEADLINE> Veteran Sharpshooter Wang Beaten in Air Pistol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Veteran sharpshooter Wang Yifu
was beaten to the second place in the men's air pistol finals here
on Monday at the Eighth National Games.
</P>
<P>
The gold medal was taken by 28-year-old Xu Dan of Jilin
province by a slim margin of 0.7 points. Xu won the top honor
with 682.7 points while the 37-year-old Wang took the silver medal
with 682.0 points.
</P>
<P>
Xu Dan had a steady performance in the 10-shot finals,
regaining his forms displayed at the latest World Shooting
Championships wherein he ranked second.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Wang was remembered for his miserable defeat in Atlanta
by squandering his comfortable edge in his last shot, and fainted
to the floor after being ranked second in the Centennial Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal in the National Games was taken by former
national record holder Tan Zhongliang of Shandong province with
681.3 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
