<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
had a slow start of the week, finishing lower in moderate trading
volume, but it managed to be off its lows of the morning.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 10 points lower at 2592 with a turnover
of 50 million NZ dollars (32 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leaders, Telecom shares led the weaker side, falling
5 cents to 808 cents. Also lower were Brierley Investment and
Carter Holt Harvey, each shedding 1 cent to 137 cents and 358
cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
But Fletcher Energy rose another 14 cents to a new high of 745
cents and Air New Zealand gained 2 cents to 281 cents.
</P>
<P>
Lion Nathan was stable at 399 cents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
