<HEADLINE> China Recalls Wu to Beef up Defence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese head coach Qi
Wusheng has recalled Shanghai Shenhua defender Wu Chengying for a
World Cup Asian Zone qualifier in Iran, the People's Daily
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese defence is gravely weakened as key defenders Fan
Zhiyi and Xie Feng are suspended for one match after they each
collected two yellow cards in the previous matches.
</P>
<P>
Wu, who is originally not selected but now in excellent form,
has left Shanghai for Tehran and is expected to arrive at the
Iranian capital on Monday.
</P>
<P>
China, which lost home to Iran 4-2, will face the same opponent
in group A on October 17. 
</P>
