<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 13 (XINHUA) -- British Queen Elizabeth II
arrived here on Sunday night for a week-long state visit on the
occasion of the 50th anniversary of India's independence, the
local press said today.
</P>
<P>
The queen, accompanied by her husband, Prince Philip, was
greeted by Indian Minister of State for External Affairs Kamala
Sinha at the Indira Gandhi International Airport here last night.
</P>
