<HEADLINE> Vietnam Gets More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Vietnam is
"on the rise in the past several months " with 38 new projects,
with total registered capital of 247 million U.S. dollars,
licensed last september , the "Vietnam News" reported today.
</P>
<P>
In the first 9 months of this year, Vietnam had 248 licensed foreign
projects with a total registered capital of 2.958 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
On comparison with the same period of last year, the number of licensed
projects increased by 13 percent, while investment was 75 percent of last
year's sum, according to the English-language daily.
</P>
<P>
The total output value of businesses with foreign investment totalled
1.75 billion dollars in nine months of the year, up 44 percent against
the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
