<HEADLINE> World Bank President Arriving to Visit Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- World Bank President James
Wolfensohn is arriving here this afternoon for a high-profile
visit which is expected to shape up the bank's future programs and
policies for Bangladesh, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
This will be the World Bank chief's second official visit to
the South Asian region, but first to Bangladesh. The trip will
also take him to Pakistan on October 18.
</P>
<P>
The tour is billed by government officials as very important
for forming the bank's policies for future lending activities and
related matters in Bangladesh which needs support from the World
Bank, one of the largest multilateral donors to the poor South
Asian country.
</P>
<P>
Wolfensohn's visit is expected to result in a more active role
of the agency in the country's future development endeavors.
</P>
<P>
During his five-day stay in Bangladesh, Wolfensohn will meet
President Shahabuddin Ahmed, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina and
other ministers.
</P>
<P>
He is also expected to visit both bank-supported and other
development projects and have discussions with direct
beneficiaries.
</P>
