<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Increase in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in Myanmar
reached 128,714 in the first six months of this year, increasing
by 10.7 percent over a year earlier, according to the latest
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of the tourists from 24 countries or regions, Japanese headed
the list during the period with 9,781, followed by French (5,782),
Thais (5,489) and Americans (2,557).
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the Myanmar Tourism Authority
also reached memorandums of understanding with Singapore and Thai
companies to respectively build a beach resort hotel each in
Kawthaung and Tachilek, both bordering Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The move was reportedly aimed at attracting more tourists from
neighboring Thailand through border points.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar also welcomed visitors from other neighbors such as
Bangladesh, China and India who traveled to the country by land
routes.
</P>
<P>
Up to the end of June this year, there were altogether 428
hotels with 9,910 rooms in Myanmar and more than 230,000 tourists
came to the country in 1996 which was designated as "Visit Myanmar
Year."
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment in Myanmar's hotels and tourism sector
amounted to 762.56 million U.S. dollars in 39 permitted projects
at the end of September this year, out of 6.44 billion dollars in
total foreign investment in the country. Singapore topped the list
of foreign investors in the sector, according to official
statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
