<HEADLINE> Property Developers Turn to Quality Apartments in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Overseas property developers
are eyeing quality apartment markets at a time as the office
market in Beijing is oversupplied, according to today's "China
Daily".
</P>
<P>
Beijing's housing price index increased from 844 points in June
to 847 in August, while the office building price index is down to
1,548 points from 1,562 in July, said a report from the China Real
Estate Index System (Creis).
</P>
<P>
Property analysts said although the apartment market is stable,
competition is still fierce on high-level apartment. Beijing
totally approved 12,621 overseas-funded companies with a committed
investment of 3.32 billion US dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
With the stable demand of luxury apartments in China's capital,
the overseas property giants, including Malaysia-based Hongleong
Co. and Dynamic Holdings Co. have been involved in apartment
development.
</P>
<P>
Dynamic Holdings opened a commercial bank in Xiamen, the first
foreign-funded bank in coastal Fujian province. It also invested
in other cities such as Shenzhen, Shanghai and Dalian. 
