<HEADLINE> Economist Stressing Government's Role in Market Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Government should let market
forces become the determinant factor of resource allocation, and
act as a watchdog for the country's overall economic situation in
market economy, today's "China Daily" quoted a speech from a
senior economist.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jinglian, a leading economist from the Development Research
Center of the State Council, delivered the speech concerning the
government's role in Asian-Pacific Economic Times, recently.
</P>
<P>
In a market Economy, governments at all levels should grant
more autonomy to State enterprises and push them into market
competition boldly, said Wu.
</P>
<P>
After 18 years of reform, non-State sectors such as private and
township enterprises have witnessed rapid development.
</P>
<P>
However, State-owned enterprises, the backbone of the national
economy, still face difficulty in reforming their management
systems and adjusting to the market economy, said the economist.
</P>
<P>
Wu emphasized that governments should focus on monitoring,
analyzing and forecasting macro-economic situations and make
timely adjustments in macro-control policies in line with the rule
of the market.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it is imperative for governments to maintain
stable, fair and competitive economic conditions by administrative
means. 
</P>
</TEXT>
