<HEADLINE> Service Apartments Become Hot in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Investors could enjoy an
lucrative return by putting money into "service apartments", which
provide hotel-type services but at lower rents, as there is a
great need for such apartments in China, today's "China Daily"
reported.
</P>
<P>
"More and more investors have begun to show interest in such
apartments as a result of surging demands for the new property
product," said Zeng Jiang of the Overseas Investment Group
(Australia) Co Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Ranking officials from over 293,500 overseas-funded firms in
the country, as well as some well-off Chinese, need those
apartments.
</P>
<P>
The cost of such apartments, usually between 50-80 square
meters, was around 75,000 US dollars for each. Investors could
take back their money in a few years under the current rental of
1.2 US dollars per square meter each day.
</P>
<P>
"The economic return of such investments is as high as 20
percent," Deng Qing, director of the China Real Estate Index
System (Creis) Office, said. 
</P>
