<HEADLINE> Chile Whitewashes Peru 4-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Marcelo Salas contributed a
hat trick as Chile crushed Peru 4-0 in a South American Zone World
Cup soccer qualifier here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chile led the first half through Salas, who scored with a
header on a pass from the right by Rodrigo Barrera in the 13th
minute.
</P>
<P>
He also netted in the 83rd and 87th minutes on passes by
Marcelo Vega and Juan Carreno respecitively.
</P>
<P>
Pedro Reyes scored the other goal in the 69th, picking a
rebound from goalkeeper Julio Balerio.
</P>
<P>
The result keeps alive the race to take fourth place in the
group and book last qualifying berth for France.
</P>
<P>
Chile and Peru now have 22 points each from 15 matches, but the
Chileans have a better goal difference.
</P>
<P>
Chile will meet Bolivia and Peru face Paraguay in their last
matches on November 16.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador, which has 21 points and will face Uruguay on the same
day, also has a slim chance to qualify for France.
</P>
<P>
Argentina, Colombia and Paraguay are already through to next
year's finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
