<DOCNO> XIE19971013.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Government to Remove Export Barriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Commerce and Industry
Ministries will speed up efforts to remove export barriers for the
first 12 categories of goods as requested by the Board of Trade,
according to Deputy Industry Minister Somphob Amatayakul.
</P>
<P>
The 12 categories are electronics, textiles, jewelry, rice,
tapioca, plastics, leather, furniture, steel, artificial flowers,
aluminum and water taps and valves.
</P>
<P>
The two ministries have been working closely together to remove
the export barriers, Somphob was quoted today by the local press
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Somphob said export regulations would be revised and export
strategies launched to penetrate new markets with future
potential, including Indochina, as well as to conduct more road
shows for Thai products.
</P>
<P>
Somphob believed that the joint effort would help boost the
export value of these goods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
