<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina, Uruguay Draw 0-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay was denied any
chance to qualify for next summer's World Cup finals after drawing
0-0 with Argentina in a South American Zone World Cup soccer
qualifier here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The draw against Argentina, who have already secured a place at
the 1998 finals, left Uruguay with 18 points from 15 games, four
points behind fourth-placed Peru with only one game left.
</P>
<P>
The top four teams in the South American World Cup qualifying
group go to France.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay will be absent for the fourth time in six tournaments
since 1978.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay's Liber Vespa was sent off following a vicious foul
midway through the second half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
