<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Golkar to Announce Presidential Candidate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's ruling party,
Golkar, plans to announce its candidate for the country's next
president next Sunday at the conclusion of its fourth leadership
meeting, the party's chairman Harmoko said.
</P>
<P>
The Golkar Central Board has drawn up a list of names, Harmoko
said here on Sunday, Antara News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko did not mention any names for the presidential election
scheduled for next March, but it is unlikely that Golkar will
nominate anyone else but the incumbent President Soeharto,
analysts said.
</P>
<P>
A number of party executives, along with leaders of
Golkar-affiliated organizations, have recently declared support
for Soeharto's nomination.
</P>
<P>
In regard to vice presidential candidate, Harmoko said Golkar
would announce it at the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR)
session next year because consultation is necessary with the
president on the candidate in view of the requirement that the
vice president has to be able to cooperate with the president.
</P>
<P>
The newly inducted 1,000 members of the MPR will convene next
March to elect a president and vice president and establish the
state policy guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Golkar has won all the six elections held under President
Soeharto. Last May in a landslide election victory, Golkar
obtained 74.3 percent of the vote, a significant increase from the
68 percent it won in 1992.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
