<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boxer Hospitalized after Loss </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Boxer Carl Wright was
hospitalized for brain injury on Monday after losing Saturday's
British light-welterweight title bout at Sheffield.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Wright, who was beaten on points by Mark
Winters, was admitted to a hospital and underwent surgery to
remove a blood clot from his brain after returning to his home in
Merseyside.
</P>
<P>
Wright's loss to Winters was his third defeat in 19 fights. He
also lost a European light-welterweight title fight on points
twelve months ago to Denmark's Soren Sondergaard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
