<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Air Force Strikes Tamil Rebel Bunkers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Air Force
destroyed Tamil rebel bunkers in the thick jungles of Mullaitivu
in Northeast Sri Lanka during the past three days.
</P>
<P>
The military's operational headquarters here said today that
the security forces repulsed all rebel attacks on government
troops and with accurate artillery fire on rebel mortar positions
they were able to destroy terrorist defenses and cause heavy
casualties to the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The effective blocking of two main supply routes of the rebels
has separated their bases in the Mullaitivu jungles and prevented
them from moving their injured to makeshift hospitals.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, the troops repulsed a rebel attack at Murunkan,
Northern Province, killing 12 rebels and injuring 30 others, the
military said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
