<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Doctors Warn People About High Blood Pressure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese medical experts and
doctors are worried about the growing number of people who have
high blood pressure but few of whom regard it as an illness or
know how to deal with it.
</P>
<P>
A recent national study found that there are 90 million people
above the age of 15 who suffer from high blood pressure. Last
year, there was a 50-percent increase in the number of people
suffering from the problem, which used to be confined to those
above the age of 50, but which is now reaching more young people
and even people in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Doctors attribute the increase to improved living standards,
changes in diet, and a lack of physical exercise. They are upset
by the fact that only half the people with high blood pressure are
actually aware of their condition and have gotten regular
treatment.
</P>
<P>
"Quite a number of people are ignorant of the illness and its
consequences," says Dr. Fang Qi, honorary president of Union
Hospital in Beijing. He said that high blood pressure and related
diseases cause about two million deaths a year, in addition to
many cases of paralysis.
</P>
<P>
"It is almost the number one killer," Dr.Fang noted, and
advised people to be more alert and to have regular check-ups when
they reach the age of 35.
</P>
<P>
A recent study of medication use by urban residents found that
30.43 percent of the people thought that the ailment did not
require any medication. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
