<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico, Canada Draw in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Canada and Mexico drew 2-2
(halftime 0-1) in a CONCACAF Zone World Cup soccer qualifier in
Edmonton, Alberta, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Enrique Alfaro scored in the 8th minute to put Mexico ahead in
the first half.
</P>
<P>
Carlo Corazzin equalized for Canada by scoring in the 55th
minute and Alex Bunbury added another nine minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the 75th minute, Mexico's Ramon Ramirez slotted the ball
into the net. 
</P>
</TEXT>
