<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Fidel Ramos is leaving today for a
five-day visit to Hong Kong, Myanmar and Laos to reinvigorate the
Philippines' economic and political relations with its three
Southeast Asian neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star
</P>
<P>
-- Australian fortune hunter Reiner Jacobi is holding nothing
but fake documents to bolster his accusation that the Ramos
administration had a hand in laundering proceeds from the sale of
Marcos gold in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Daily Inquirer
</P>
<P>
-- All the stories about the "Marcos gold" are true, according
to the American treasure hunter who once dug unsuccessfully for
the precious metal at Fort Santiago in Intramuros, Manila.
</P>
</TEXT>
