<HEADLINE> Japan Trade Surplus Up 77.7 Percent in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TOKYO, October 13 (Xinhua) - Japan's current account surplus
in August rose 77.7 percent from a year earlier to 817.8 billion
yen (about 6.8 billion US Dollars), the Finance Ministry announced
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The surplus in merchandise trade alone rose 68.0 percent
from the same month a year earlier to 912.6 billion yen, with
exports growing 13.8 percent to 3,826.5 yen and imports up only
3.4 percent to 2,913.8 billion yen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
