<HEADLINE> Jansher Through, Zubair Pulls out Egyptian Squash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 12 (Xinhua) -- World number one Jansher Khan of
Pakistan defeated German qualifier Simon Frenz in 27 minutes,
winning his opening round match 15-6, 15-7. 15-3 at the Egyptian
Open men's squash tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile Jansher's compatriot Zubair Jahan withdrew against
England's Danny Meddings when trailing by two games and 11-5 down
in the third.
</P>
<P>
England's prospects for the defence of the world team title
took a knock when Chris Walker, the second highest world ranked
Englishman and the seventh seed here, was beaten by 9-15, 15-9,
5-15, 17-14, 15-9 by Nick Taylor, an English qualifier world
ranked only 39. 
</P>
</TEXT>
