<DOCNO> XIE19971013.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic Beats Rusedski to Win Austrian Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia
rallied from two sets down to beat Briton Greg Rusedski 3-2 in the
final of the CA Trophy tennis tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Croat triumphed 3-6, 6-7 (4-7), 7-6 (7-5), 6-2 and 6-3 over
the world number four and moves from ninth to fifth in the world
rankings.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski missed 17 break points -- including three in the final
game, while Ivanisevic served 37 aces to Rusedski's 36.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski capitalised on a series of errors to take the first
set with a single break in the sixth game.
</P>
<P>
Although he was the better server in the second he failed to
use two break points in the fifth game and one in the 11th as it
went to a tie-break.
</P>
<P>
Two double faults by the Croat, who has been struggling with a
cold this week, decided the tiebreak in Rusedski's favour 7-4.
</P>
<P>
The third also went to the tiebreak, Ivanisevic taking it and
the momentum swung his way when he won the fourth set 6-2 with two
breaks.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski appeared to recuperate and broke for a 1-0 final set
lead, but he lost his serve at 2-2 and 5-3.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic fought off three break points before taking the
match as the Briton weakly netted a return. 
</P>
</TEXT>
