<HEADLINE> British Queen Leaves for New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Queen of Britain Elizabeth II
and her husband, the Duke of Edinburgh, left here tonight for New
Delhi at the end of her six-day visit to Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan saw the royal guests
off at the Chaklala Airbase.
</P>
<P>
The queen arrived here last Tuesday on a six-day state visit,
her second to the country in the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
During her stay here the queen held meetings with Pakistani
President Farooq Leghari and Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and
addressed a joint session of the parliament.  
</P>
</TEXT>
