<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Lufthansa Airline Privatized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Privatization of Germany's
national airline Lufthansa has been completed in success, an
international bank group announced in Frankfurt today.
</P>
<P>
The Bonn government is expected to gain some 4.7 billion
marks (2.7 billion U.S. dollars) from the sales of its remaining
35.7 percent stake in the company, said the bank group in charge
of coordinating the subscriptions.
</P>
<P>
The placement of the remaining 143 million Lufthansa shares
held by the government, which began about two weeks ago, had
become a "complete success", the group said.
</P>
<P>
It said demand for the shares had more than doubled the total
subscription offer, and that over half of the shares had been
ordered by private investors with the rest going to large local
and foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The final sales price had been set at 33.30 marks per share,
but private investors would be able to buy them at 32.30 marks,
the group announced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
